<sub><italic>ijk</italic></sub> represents optional weights such as distance from the gene transcription start site (TSS) [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR24">24</xref>]. An analysis where no weights <italic>w</italic>
<sub><italic>ijk</italic></sub> are used is shown in Additional file <xref rid="MOESM1" ref-type="media">1</xref>: Figure S2 where an R<sup>2</sup> = 0.99 between final scores with and without weighting and nearly identical final modules and annotations in Additional file <xref rid="MOESM2" ref-type="media">2</xref>: Tables S14–S15, indicate that SMITE is robust for choices of <italic>w</italic>
