<italic>.</italic> In a high-resolution epigenomic assay like HELP-tagging, it is possible to have as many as ~2000 data points (<italic>p</italic>-values) associated with a large region like a gene body. Because aggregated scores increase as the number of <italic>p</italic>-values within a genomic interval increases, SMITE implements a quantile-permutation adjustment, whereby a specific <italic>R</italic>
